<body>
    <h1>Project Beacon Proof of Concept</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-Abstract">Abstract</h1>
<h1 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-QuestionstoAnswer">Questions to Answe=
r</h1>
<p>The point of this POC is to find concrete answers to the following quest=
ions, and use that to determine if there is anything that would prevent Bea=
con from going forwards.</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>What Android permissions would an app require for different modes of ope=
ration?</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>What would an app require to send data?</p></li>
<li>
<p>What would an app require to perform a Bluetooth Scan?</p></li>
<li>
<p>What would an app require to have a task running in the background?</p><=
/li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>What is the user experience of an app utilizing the Beacon SDK?</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>What prompts will the user receive?</p></li>
<li>
<p>What information can the see about the app running?</p></li>
<li>
<p>What happens if a user does not grant the permissions we need?</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>Privacy and Security</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>What data are we able to collect from the app / SDK?</p></li>
<li>
<p>Are we limited in how we use this data?</p></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<h1 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-POCComponents">POC Components</h1>
<p>The functional elements to be built as part of this project are:</p>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-AndroidSDK">Android SDK</h2>
<p>A basic SDK that allows for either sending or receiving Bluetooth data. =
The SDK should have the ability to make calls the the server element to get=
 SecureIDs, or to send collected SecureIDs to the server.</p>
<p>All actions should be performed as a background task, and not require th=
e app using the SDK to be in the foreground, if possible.</p>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-AndroidReferenceApp">Android Referenc=
e App</h2>
<p>A simple app with at least one screen that implements the SDK. Should de=
monstrate the basics of what the user experience of using an app implementi=
ng the Android SDK would be.</p>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-BeaconServer">Beacon Server</h2>
<p>A REST endpoint or endpoints that can either provide SecureIDs or receiv=
e SecureIDs and decrypt them. Should implement basic logging to be able to =
show it is sending / receiving data, but no UI is required</p>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-KioskReference">Kiosk Reference</h2>
<p>Because the RMN kiosk is fully under T-Mobile control, we are more confi=
dent we can implement whatever is required for Beacon. To simplify the POC,=
 the reference Kiosk will be code running on a developer laptop. The Kiosk =
app will, at a minimum, do the following:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Scan for Bluetooth signals and collect relevant data from broadcasting B=
luetooth devices</p></li>
<li>
<p>Send it=E2=80=99s own SecureID</p></li>
<li>
<p>Connect to the Beacon Server to get SecureIDs to send</p></li>
<li>
<p>Send collected SecureIDs to the server</p></li>
</ol>
<p>The Kiosk app will implement basic logging to show what data it receives=
, but will not have a UI component.</p>
<h1 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-ProjectCompletionGoals">Project Compl=
etion Goals</h1>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-Goal#1:Demo-AppSending">Goal #1: Demo=
 - App Sending</h2>
<p>Demonstrate an Android app that implements the Beacon SDK. The SDK will =
fetch one or more SecureIDs from the server, and begin broadcasting them.</=
p>
<p>The Kiosk will receive these SecureIDs via Bluetooth. The Kiosk will the=
n send the collected SecureIDs to the Server</p>
<p>The server will provide SecureIDs to the device and receive SecureIDs fr=
om the kiosk. The server will decrypt and log received data.</p>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-Goal#2:Demo-AppReceiving">Goal #2: De=
mo - App Receiving</h2>
<p>Demonstrate an Android app that implements the Beacon SDK. The SDK will =
scan for relevant Bluetooth signals containing a SecureID. The SDK will sen=
d these SecureIDs to the server.</p>
<p>The Kiosk will receive SecureIDs from the Server. it will then broadcast=
 these SecureIDs via Bluetooth.</p>
<p>The server will provide SecureIDs to the kiosk and receive SecureIDs fro=
m the device. The server will decrypt and log received data.</p>
<h1 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-OutofScope">Out of Scope</h1>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-iOS">iOS</h2>
<p>There are additional challenges with iOS development. While we would eve=
ntually like to expand Beacon to iOS, and the underlying Bluetooth Low Ener=
gy protocols are functionally identical between iOS and Android, this is cu=
rrently out of scope</p>
<h2 id=3D"ProjectBeaconProofofConcept-RMNKiosk">RMN Kiosk</h2>
<p>The development environment around the RMN kiosk is still being develope=
d by the RMN team. To avoid adding unneeded complexity to this POC, we will=
 not use a =E2=80=98real=E2=80=99 RMN kiosk, and instead have a developer l=
aptop serve it=E2=80=99s role in the POC.</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
    </div>
</body>
